article.headline: S. Dakota St. 71, Centenary 58
article.story: BROOKINGS, S.D. -- Garrett Callahan scored 20 points to lead South Dakota State to a 71-58 win over Centenary in the Summit League opener for both teams on Thursday. Callahan was 9-for-13 from line for the Jackrabbits (4-5, 1-0), who made 30 of 39 free throws in the game. Centenary (2-7, 0-1) was 11-for-20. It trailed 52-50 with 3:58 remaining, but SDSU went on a 19-8 run down the stretch. Anthony Cordova had 15 points and Dale Moss added 12 points and 12 rebounds for SDSU. Centenary was led by Chase Adams with 21 points. Nick Stallings and Roman Tubner added 10 each.
